question.text: Resistance of a <math><mn>0.1</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"> </mi><mi mathvariant="normal">K</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi></math> solution in a conductance cell is <math><mn>300</mn><mi mathvariant="normal"> </mi><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">h</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi></math> and specific conductance of <math><mn>0.1</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"> </mi><mi mathvariant="normal">K</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi></math> is <math><mn>1.33</mn><mi mathvariant="normal"> </mi><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><msup><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">h</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mi mathvariant="normal">c</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> . The resistance of <math><mn>0.1</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"> </mi><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi></math> solution in the same cell is <math><mn>400</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">ohm</mi></math>. The equivalent conductance of the <math><mn>0.1</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">M</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"> </mi><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">l</mi></math> solution (in <math><mi mathvariant="normal">o</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">h</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">c</mi><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>/</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">g</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">m</mi></mrow></mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">e</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">q</mi><mo>.</mo></math>) is
